Transcription.Text: Rodin's Ghost will not be laid. Ralph Brown began as a social realist sculptor infusing tenderness into a gawky mother fondling a child, an infant bowling a hoop. But recently his sculptural conceptions, carried out in ciment fondu for bronze, have become more complex.
